FBIS3-37067 "drsov030_f_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 National Affairs Crimean Parties Form Bloc, Appeal for Coalition Government WS1402111094 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 0900 GMT 14 Feb 94 WS1402111094 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] Crimean political parties of centrist orientation -- the Union for Support of the Crimean Republic, the Party of Democratic Revival of the Crimea, the Democratic Party of the Crimea, and the Civic Forum of the Crimea -- have announced the formation of a new party bloc called "Sozidaniye" [the Creation]. The bloc is ready to share the responsibility for drawing up and implementing the program of economic reform in the autonomous republic with Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov. The first initiative of the new bloc was an appeal to Yuriy Meshkov to form a coalition interparty government. The leaders of "Sozidaniye" intend that the bloc will join the Kuchma-Hrynyov interregional bloc.
